BMW Aims for 25% Increase in U.S. Sales, Automotive News Reports

-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 
2011-12-11T13:19:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/bmw-aims-for-25-increase-in-u-s-sales-automotive-news-reports.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  aims to
increase U.S. sales by 25 percent from about 240,000 units this
year,  Automotive News Europe  reported, citing an interview with
Ludwig Willisch, head of the its North American operations.  Willisch said BMW is targeting the increase to 300,000 unit
sales in the mid-term, the report said. A person at the company
said the aim is to reach that figure by 2013-14, according to
the report, which didnâ€™t specify who supplied the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
